<paragraph blockId="15.[189,455,1395,1456]" box="[189,455,1430,1456]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
BODY LENGTH. 
<quantity box="[357,450,1430,1456]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.8" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" unit="mm" value="4.8">4.8 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[189,1399,1495,1662]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
HEAD. Head slightly wider than long. Integument black, except part of mandibles dark reddish-brown. Face sparsely covered with long, greyish, erect hair (
<figureCitation box="[832,927,1530,1556]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="16.[189,231,1958,1984]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,582,1915]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[189,1399,582,1917]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Fig. 8. Scrapter gessorum sp. nov., ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Metasoma (dorsal view). C. Head. D. Head (SEM). E. Thorax (dorsal view). F. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860612" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860612/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Fig. 8C</figureCitation>
). Clypeus almost flat with dense large, shallow punctation (i = 1.5–2.0 d); surface between punctures apically smooth or only superficially sculptured, shiny, basally more heavily sculptured and matt (
<figureCitation box="[911,980,1601,1627]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="16.[189,231,1958,1984]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,582,1915]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[189,1399,582,1917]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Fig. 8. Scrapter gessorum sp. nov., ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Metasoma (dorsal view). C. Head. D. Head (SEM). E. Thorax (dorsal view). F. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860612" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860612/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
C–D). Malar area medially narrow, almost linear. Antenna dorsally blackish-brown, ventrally yellowish-brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[189,1398,1701,1869]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
MESOSOMA. Integument black. Mesoscutal disc between punctures with superficial sculpture, shiny; disc very sparsely (i = 3–5 d), finely and shallowly punctate (
<figureCitation box="[869,938,1737,1763]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="16.[189,231,1958,1984]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,582,1915]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[189,1399,582,1917]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Fig. 8. Scrapter gessorum sp. nov., ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Metasoma (dorsal view). C. Head. D. Head (SEM). E. Thorax (dorsal view). F. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860612" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860612/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
E–F). Metanotum about 3/4 as long as basal area of propodeum, apically with indistinct, narrow, carinate depression (
<figureCitation box="[1146,1239,1772,1798]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="16.[189,231,1958,1984]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,582,1915]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[189,1399,582,1917]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Fig. 8. Scrapter gessorum sp. nov., ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Metasoma (dorsal view). C. Head. D. Head (SEM). E. Thorax (dorsal view). F. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860612" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860612/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Fig. 8F</figureCitation>
). Propodeum basilaterally with shallow carination (
<figureCitation box="[627,715,1807,1833]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="16.[189,231,1958,1984]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,582,1915]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[189,1399,582,1917]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Fig. 8. Scrapter gessorum sp. nov., ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Metasoma (dorsal view). C. Head. D. Head (SEM). E. Thorax (dorsal view). F. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860612" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860612/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Fig. 8F</figureCitation>
). Mesoscutum, scutellum, metanotum, mesepisternum and propodeum sparsely covered with short, greyish, erect hair (
<figureCitation box="[893,987,1842,1868]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="16.[189,231,1958,1984]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,582,1915]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[189,1399,582,1917]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Fig. 8. Scrapter gessorum sp. nov., ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Metasoma (dorsal view). C. Head. D. Head (SEM). E. Thorax (dorsal view). F. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860612" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860612/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Fig. 8A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[189,888,1908,1934]" lastBlockId="16.[189,1399,267,364]" lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="17" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
WINGS. Yellowish-brown; wing venation and stigma brown. LEGS. Integument black to dark reddish-brown; fore tibia anteriorly dominantly yellowish-brown, mid tibia basally with small yellow spot (
<figureCitation box="[637,733,302,329]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="16.[189,231,1958,1984]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,582,1915]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[189,1399,582,1917]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Fig. 8. Scrapter gessorum sp. nov., ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Metasoma (dorsal view). C. Head. D. Head (SEM). E. Thorax (dorsal view). F. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860612" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860612/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Fig. 8A</figureCitation>
). Vestiture greyish-white, scopa greyish-white, dorsally blackish-brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[189,1399,403,535]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
METASOMA. Integument black, apical margins of terga sometimes narrowly translucent dark reddishbrown (
<figureCitation box="[279,370,438,464]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="16.[189,231,1958,1984]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,582,1915]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[189,1399,582,1917]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Fig. 8. Scrapter gessorum sp. nov., ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Metasoma (dorsal view). C. Head. D. Head (SEM). E. Thorax (dorsal view). F. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860612" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860612/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Fig. 8B</figureCitation>
). Disc of T1 without hair; following terga with increasingly more and longer hair; apical tergal hair bands missing on all terga (
